  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>Breakfast really sets you up for the day here. Enjoy a breakfast buffet with fresh pastries, cold meats, cheeses and fresh fruit with some hot choices too.</p>
<p>The evening meals are full of tasty traditional dishes with influences from the Aosta Valley. There are four delicious courses each evening, exactly what you need after a day on the slopes. </p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>Set in the traditional village of Gressoney La Trinitè, the Hotel Lo Sciattolo enjoys a peaceful location near to the village square and a short walk to the Punta Jolanda lift. There is a shuttle service which runs between Gressoney and Staffal, so you don't have to worry about walking too far in ski boots!  As soon as you arrive, the team will make you feel at home. They really go all out to make sure everyone’s holiday is special. </p>
<h2>Alpine hotel</h2>
<p>The hotel has a real Alpine feel to it, with warm wood and traditional touches. There are 35 unique rooms, each with cosy mountain decor and modern conveniences, with rooms sleeping up to four, this is an excellent choice for your next family ski holiday. After a day of adventures, we love chilling out by the open fire in the warm and welcoming lounge-bar area. </p>
<h2>Food and drink</h2>
<p>After building up an appetite all day, dinners at the hotel are something to look forward to. The restaurant serves fantastic Italian food, including traditional dishes from the Valle d'Aosta. Many of the products used are locally sourced, including a variety of jams, chestnuts, compotes which come from the family's artisan business, Alpenzu.  The Hotel Lo Scoiattolo has a vegetable garden 'KM0', this includes various seasonal ingredients including chard, zucchini, green beans, leeks, cabbage, celery and carrots, herbs and potatoes: all products that the kitchen team use to prepare delicious dishes. The products are freshly picked and are not treated, retaining their fragrance and flavor. </p>
<p>Before retreating to bed, head to the bar for a nightcap - embrace gressonara traditions and try a grappa or Genepy. You can also enjoy a glass of wine from the well stocked Winery which includes typical products from the <a data-udi="umb://document/44c205035969462abff34bd958a9f9af" href="/{localLink:umb://document/44c205035969462abff34bd958a9f9af}" title="Aosta Valley Ski Area">Aosta Valley</a>. </p>
<h2>Wellness and relaxation</h2>
<p>Make sure you leave time to sit back and relax, the hotel has a lovely wellness area open each afternoon. Soothe any aches and pains in the jacuzzi, unwind in the sauna or Turkish bath, and enjoy resting in the relaxation area with a herbal tea. For a little extra treat, massages and wellness treatments are available for an additional fee. </p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 1 hour 45 mins from Turin airport.</p>]]></description>
